    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>BlueStar Appliances We Repair</h3>

      <h4>BlueStar Range Repair</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Burners that will not ignite or will not stay lit</li>
        <li>Weak flame, uneven flame, or inconsistent heat output</li>
        <li>Oven not heating, overheating, or not holding temperature</li>
        <li>Broiler not working properly</li>
        <li>Ignition problems, gas valve issues, or control problems</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>BlueStar Rangetop & Cooktop Repair</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Clicking igniters or burners that spark continuously</li>
        <li>Poor burner performance or uneven heating</li>
        <li>Gas smell or burner operation concerns</li>
        <li>Damaged burner components, grates, or ignition parts</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>BlueStar Wall Oven Repair</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Slow preheating or inaccurate baking temperatures</li>
        <li>Uneven cooking or convection performance issues</li>
        <li>Door hinge, seal, or closing problems</li>
        <li>Control panel faults, display issues, or error symptoms</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>BlueStar Refrigerator & Freezer Repair</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Not cooling properly or fluctuating interior temperatures</li>
        <li>Frost buildup, airflow issues, or defrost-related problems</li>
        <li>Leaks, unusual noises, or compressor-related symptoms</li>
        <li>Ice maker or temperature control concerns</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>BlueStar Ventilation Hood Repair</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Fan not operating correctly or reduced airflow</li>
        <li>Lighting or switch malfunctions</li>
        <li>Noise, vibration, or control problems</li>
        <li>Performance issues affecting smoke and odor removal</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Common BlueStar Appliance Problems We Diagnose</h3>
      <p>
        BlueStar appliances are built differently from standard residential units, and
        their repair needs often require a more specialized approach. We commonly diagnose
        issues involving burner ignition, unstable flame, oven temperature inaccuracy,
        heat regulation problems, gas-related performance issues, cooling problems,
        failed controls, worn hinges, damaged seals, and ventilation system malfunctions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Because BlueStar appliances are designed for high performance, even a small issue
        can affect cooking results, temperature control, and long-term reliability. That is
        why careful diagnosis matters just as much as the repair itself.
      </p>
    </section>

